shipping.allDelivery: All delivery times are estimates and are not guaranteed. Shipments may be affected by weather-related delays, carrier limitations or other events outside of our control.
shipping.allSales: All sales with Flight Club are final. Flight Club is a ship-to-verify and consignment marketplace, meaning all items we carry and offer on this site are generally provided by independent owners. Once an item sells, either online or in one of our stores, the owner receives payment for their merchandise. Because of this, we are unable to process returns or exchanges.
shipping.deliveryAndProcessing: Delivery and processing speeds vary by pricing options. "Lowest Price" orders may ship to Flight Club first for verification and typically take 7-10 business days (M-F, excluding holidays) to reach buyers located in the 48 contiguous states. Excluding deliveries to PO boxes and military bases, it will typically take 3-5 business days (M-F, excluding holidays) for a "Fastest To You" item, ordered before 2 PM ET with standard shipping, to be delivered to a buyer located in the 48 contiguous states. For “Fastest To You” items ordered after 2 PM ET with standard shipping, it will take 4-6 business days to be delivered to a buyer located in the 48 contiguous states.
shipping.forSneakers: For sneakers, you may cancel your order within 3 hours of placing it or before the order is confirmed by the seller, whichever comes first. If 3 hours have passed from when you placed the order and/or the seller has confirmed the order, then the order cannot be canceled. If neither has occurred, simply access your order via “Track My Order” or “My Account,” click “Cancel Order” and follow the instructions.
shipping.holidayDelivery: Holiday delivery estimates for Fastest to You orders are not guaranteed and are only applicable to the contiguous US, excluding PO boxes and military bases. Shipments may be affected by weather-related delays, carrier limitations or other events outside of our control.
shipping.ifYouChecked: If you checked out as a guest, you will need to create a Flight Club account to manage or cancel your order.
shipping.ifYouHave: If you have any questions with regard to sizing or condition of a specific product on our site, please <0>contact us</0> before committing to purchase.
shipping.nextDayIs: “Next Day” is a shipping option for “Fastest To You” items that is available only to buyers located in the 48 contiguous states, excluding PO boxes and military bases. It will typically take 1 business day for a “Fastest To You” item ordered before 2 PM ET with “Next Day” shipping to be delivered to a buyer located in the 48 contiguous states. It will typically take 2 business days for a “Fastest To You” item ordered after 2 PM ET with “Next Day” shipping to be delivered to a buyer located in the 48 contiguous states. Estimated delivery times do not apply to international orders, which vary by country.
shipping.onceYourOrder: Once your order ships, you will receive an email notification with your tracking information. International customers are responsible for any additional fees or taxes after an item ships. We do our best to protect international customers from incurring additional fees, but cannot guarantee against any unexpected expenses.
shipping.pleaseFeelFree: Please feel free to <0>contact us</0> with any questions.
shipping.refundsAreOnly: Refunds are only processed based on fulfillment errors, such as incorrectly shipped or missing items.
shipping.theRiskOf: The risk of loss and title for items purchased by you passes to you upon our delivery of the items to the carrier. faq.howToFindCodeBody: <0>Please login to your online bank account and search for the Flight Club transaction. There you will find a five digit code after the asterisk at the end of the descriptor. It should look something like this:</0> <1>FLIGHTCLUB#XXXX *12345</1> <0>You may need to expand the transaction details to see the full source.</0>
faq.howToFindCodeTitle: How do I find my statement code?
faq.whatCodeBody: If you’re having trouble finding the statement code, you can send us a screenshot of your statement with the Flight Club transaction and we can assist you. Or you can contact your bank and ask them to locate the Flight Club transaction to find the five digit code after the asterisk. As an alternative, you can ask them for the autherization code. The authorization code is the code that the banks issue to merchants that allows us to charge the card.
faq.whatCodeTitle: What if I can't find the code?
faq.whyCodeBody: It is our goal to process your order as quickly as possible. When an order is submitted, some orders are placed in review status while our payments team reviews the purchase activity for any potential fraudulent activity to protect both the buyer and seller. In order to process your order, we need a little more information from you.

jobs.jobsIntro: 世界トップのスニーカーマーケットプレイスであるFlight Club。オンラインに加え、ニューヨーク、ロサンゼルス、マイアミの実店舗を通して、人気のスニーカー＆スポーツウェアを日々に何千人ものお客様にお届けしています。委託販売も充実しており、毎日何百ものスニーカーを配送＆店頭にて受け取り、査定を行なっています。このワークプレイスの活気をさらに高めるため、カスタマーサービス、販売フロア、ストックルームの各チームに加わっていただける方を募集しています。Flight Club チームへの参加にご興味のある方は、是非ご応募ください。

faq.whatCodeBody: 明細コードが見つからない場合は、Flight Clubへのお支払いが記載された明細書のスクリーンショットを送信いただければ、サポートさせていただきます。または、Flight Clubへのお支払い履歴およびアスタリスクの後にある5桁のコードの検索を、お客様の銀行にお問い合わせいただくことも可能です。あるいは、銀行に認証コードの確認をご依頼することもできます。認証コードとは、カードへの請求を許可できるように銀行が加盟店に発行するコードです。
faq.whatCodeTitle: コードが見つからない場合は？
faq.whyCodeBody: 当社は、できるだけ迅速にお客様のご注文の処理を行うことを心がけております。ご注文が送信されると、一部のご注文は審査過程に置かれ、購入者と出品者の両方を保護する目的で購入動向に不正行為の可能性がないかを専門のチームが審査します。ご注文の処理を行うために、詳細な情報をご提供いただく必要があります。

hits.name: Air Jordan 5 Retro SE 'UNC'
hits.story_html: The Air Jordan 5 Retro SE ‘UNC’ showcases a familiar pastel hue inspired by Michael Jordan’s alma mater. The upper is crafted from University Blue nubuck with tonal TPU eyelets, ventilated quarter-panel netting and a woven jock tag at the heel. An embroidered Jumpman decorates the tongue, rendered in a reflective silver finish for added visibility in low-light conditions. Lightweight cushioning comes courtesy of a black polyurethane midsole, accented with speckled shark-tooth detailing and fitted with a visible Air-sole unit in the heel. Underfoot, a translucent herringbone-traction outsole provides optimal grip.
hits.story: The Tar Heels’ school colors are honored in the Air Jordan 5 Retro SE ‘UNC.’ With shark-tooth details on the black midsole, the University Blue nubuck leather upper is complemented by breathable netting at the quarter panel. The tongue is adorned with a stitched Jumpman in reflective silver. Support and traction underfoot are supplied by a PU midsole in black with an exposed Air-sole unit in the heel atop a herringbone-patterned clear outsole. a translucent herringbone-traction outsole.

hits.name: Air Jordan 5 Retro 'Aqua'
hits.story_html: The Air Jordan 5 Retro ‘Aqua’ showcases a distinctive color scheme that recalls an AJ5 PE made for Chris Paul during his time with the New Orleans Hornets. The legacy silhouette makes use of a black nubuck upper with translucent quarter-panel netting for improved breathability. A bright teal Jumpman decorates the back heel and silver reflective tongue. Anchoring the sneaker is a black polyurethane midsole, featuring speckled yellow shark-tooth detailing and visible Air-sole cushioning in the heel. Finished in a vibrant turquoise hue, a translucent rubber outsole yields durable traction.
hits.story: Early-era AJ5 PE's reminiscent of Chris Paul's New Orleans Hornets tenure are revisited in the Air Jordan 5 Retro ‘Aqua.’ The upper in solid black nubuck is brightened by the bright-yellow specked shark-tooth elements on the black midsole and the turquoise outsole detailing. Branding is subtle, with the signature Jumpman on the metallic tongue backed with cushioned teal which repeats at the heel. Clear quarter panel netting provides ventilation and Air-sole cushioning delivers easy wear on and off the court.

hits.name: Wmns Air Jordan 5 Retro 'Dunk on Mars'
hits.story_html: The Women’s Air Jordan 5 Retro ‘Dunk on Mars’ pays homage to Spike Lee’s alter ego, Mars Blackmon, whose planetary namesake is also known as the Red Planet. To that end, the heritage silhouette sports a scarlet suede upper, accented with translucent quarter-panel netting and contrasting black eyelets. Jumpman branding appears on the silver reflective tongue, while ‘23’ is embroidered on the lateral heel. The sneaker rides on an Air-assisted black polyurethane midsole with fiery shark-tooth detailing in orange and red. Underfoot, a yellow-tinged translucent rubber outsole features a herringbone tread for optimized grip.
hits.story: Mars Blackmon, the iconic Spike Lee character who co-starred with #23 in many ads, was the inspiration for the Women’s Air Jordan 5 Retro ‘Dunk on Mars.’ The legacy shoe's Air-assisted black midsole in leaping red-and-orange flames is topped with a suede upper in brilliant scarlet-red with clear netting on the quarter panel and a see-through lace lock securing black laces. The ubiquitous Jumpman decorates the tongue in the silver metallic reflective tongue, and a stitched ‘23’ appears on the lateral heel.

hits.name: Air Jordan 5 Retro 'Racer Blue'
hits.story_html: The Air Jordan 5 Retro ‘Racer Blue’ adds color-popped accents to a stealthy colorway of the venerable 1990 silhouette, designed by Tinker Hatfield and introduced to the world by Mars Blackmon. The mid-top makes use of a black nubuck upper with tonal TPU eyelets, translucent quarter panel netting and a reflective silver tongue. The latter features contrasting hits of royal blue on the embroidered Jumpman and interior lining. Lightweight cushioning arrives via a blue polyurethane midsole, embellished with black shark tooth detailing and fitted with visible Air-sole cushioning in the heel. A translucent rubber outsole provides grippy traction underfoot.
hits.story: Adding some color to the 1990s silhouette designed by Tinker Hatfield and brought to the public by Mars Blackmon is the Air Jordan 5 Retro 'Racer Blue.' It features a black nubuck upper with tonal TPU eyelets, translucent quarter panel netting and a reflective silver tongue. The mid-top's latter has contrasting touches of royal blue on the embroidered Jumpman and interior lining. The blue polyurethane midsole has lightweight cushioning with black shark tooth detailing and visible Air-sole cushioning in the heel. It rides on a translucent rubber outsole for a better grip.

hits.name: Air Jordan 5 Retro 'Green Bean' 2022
hits.story_html: The 2022 edition of the Air Jordan 5 Retro ‘Green Bean’ brings back a distinctive two-tone colorway initially released in 2006. Like the original, the mid-top carries a light grey nubuck upper entirely coated in a reflective finish. Bright green accents make their way to the interior lining and the embroidered Jumpman logo that decorate the heel and tongue. The vivid hue is repeated on the shark-tooth detailing that enlivens the dark grey polyurethane midsole. Underfoot, a translucent herringbone-tread rubber outsole provides grippy traction. The Jordan 5 'Green Bean' 2022 will release on May 28, 2022.
hits.story: Bringing back a two-tone colorway first released in 2006 is the 2022 edition of the Air Jordan 5 'Green Bean.' Similar to the original mid-top, a light grey nubuck upper is entirely coated in a reflective finish. Bright green accents make their way to the interior lining and the embroidered Jumpman logo on the heel and tongue, which is repeated on the shark-tooth detailing that enlivens the dark grey polyurethane midsole. It's built on a translucent herringbone-tread rubber outsole. The Jordan 5 'Green Bean' 2022 will drop on May 28, 2022.

hits.name: Air Jordan 5 Retro 'Raging Bull' 2021
hits.story_html: The 2021 reissue of the Air Jordan 5 Retro ‘Raging Bull’ brings back a beloved colorway originally released as one-half of 2009’s Air Jordan 5 Raging Bulls Pack. The shoe’s defining feature is a plush Varsity Red suede upper, equipped with black eyelets and a Jumpman-branded reflective silver tongue. The heel overlay displays a second Jumpman logo and an embroidered 23 on the lateral side. A visible Nike Air heel unit enhances the polyurethane midsole, accented with red-tipped shark tooth detailing and supported by an icy translucent outsole.
hits.story: Originally released in 2009 as part of the two-shoe Raging Bulls pack, the Air Jordan 5 Retro 'Raging Bull' 2021 brings back one of those colorways with this April 2021 release. The shoe's suede upper appears entirely in Varsity Red, contrasted by black eyelets and highlighted by a reflective silver tongue. Mesh inserts maintain the classic Jordan aesthetic, with a toggle lacing system securing the fit. Underfoot, the polyurethane midsole includes visible Air in the heel for cushioning, highlighted by the white and red shark-tooth detailing on the forefoot.

hits.name: Air Jordan 5 Retro SE 'Craft'
hits.story_html: The Air Jordan 5 Retro SE ‘Craft’ updates the legacy silhouette with a subtle color palette and a refreshed build. Crafted from taupe-colored suede and textile, the upper is secured with two-tone laces and accented with translucent quarter-panel netting. Orange textile lines the tongue, matching the signature Jumpman that decorates the exterior. A second Jumpman icon graces the heel overlay in grey embroidery. The mid-top rides on an off-white polyurethane midsole, featuring speckled shark-tooth detailing and a visible Air-sole unit in the heel. Underfoot, a translucent herringbone-pattern rubber outsole yields superior stop-and-go traction.
hits.story: The Air Jordan 5 Retro SE 'Craft' modernizes a classic Jordan design. Constructed from a combination of suede and textile in a taupe hue, the upper is fastened with two-tone laces and features clear quarter-panel mesh. The tongue is lined with orange textile material and is decorated with the iconic Jumpman logo. The mid-top silhouette is mounted on An off-white polyurethane midsole with speckled shark-tooth detailing and a visible Air-sole unit in the heel provides support. The translucent herringbone-traction rubber outsole provides excellent traction for quick pivots on the hardwood.

hits.name: Air Jordan 5 Retro 'Oreo' 2021
hits.story_html: The 2021 edition of the Air Jordan 5 Retro ‘Oreo’ 2021 brings back a simple two-tone colorway first released in 2013. The build is faithful to the original, featuring a black suede upper with tonal TPU eyelets, translucent quarter panel netting and a grey Jumpman embroidered on the tongue. Contrasting white hits appear on the collar lining, interior tongue and Jumpman heel branding. The mid-top sits on a white polyurethane midsole with a visible Air unit nestled in the heel and black shark-tooth detailing dusted in white speckles. Underfoot, an icy rubber outsole delivers stop-and-go traction.
hits.story: Originally released in 2013, the Air Jordan 5 Retro brings back the two-tone look with this 2021 release. Faithful to the original, the shoe's upper is built with suede, finished in black and contrasted by white on the collar lining, interior tongue and heel branding. Translucent netting marks the quarter panel, while tonal TPU eyelets bolster the lacing system. Underfoot, a white polyurethane midsole includes visible Air in the heel to provide cushioning, with speckled shark-tooth detailing accenting the forefoot. An icy translucent rubber outsole offers traction and deviates from the black-and-white design.

hits.name: Air Jordan 3 Retro 'Washington Wizards'
hits.story_html: The Air Jordan 3 Retro ‘Washington Wizards’ showcases a familiar design based on a PE colorway that Michael Jordan wore during his time in D.C. Featuring color blocking reminiscent of the OG ‘True Blue’ edition from 1988, the classic silhouette makes use of a white tumbled leather upper with grey elephant-print overlays at the toe and heel. Contrasting blue accents appear on the interior lining, molded eyelets, and the raised Jumpman logo that decorates the heel tab. A second Jumpman graces the tongue in copper-colored embroidery, matching the circular eyelets that dot the forefoot. The mid-top is mounted on a two-tone polyurethane midsole, equipped with a visible Air-sole heel unit and supported by a durable grey rubber outsole.
hits.story: A design inspired by a PE colorway that Michael Jordan wore during his time in D.C. distinguishes the Air Jordan 3 Retro 'Washington Wizards.’ The classic silhouette is reminiscent of the OG 'True Blue' 1988 edition and features a tumbled leather upper in stark white with the toe and heel displaying grey elephant-print overlays. The sneaker is complemented by contrasting blue accents on the molded eyelets, interior lining and raised Jumpman logo on the heel tab. A copper-colored stitched Jumpman also appears on the tongue, matching the forefoot’s circular eyelets. A durable grey rubber outsole supports the two-tone polyurethane midsole with a visible Air-sole heel unit underfoot.

hits.name: Marvel x Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG 'Next Chapter'
hits.story_html: The Marvel x Air Jordan 1 Retro High OG ‘Next Chapter' delivers a collaborative colorway tied to the animated film 'Spider-Man: Across the Spider-Verse.’ A play on the original ‘Chicago’ colorway, this reimagined take on the sneaker icon features a white leather upper with black patent leather on the collar and Swoosh.
